DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add( t=>'Real' );
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

## make sure that this problem, Q03.pg, and Q23.pg, if used, have
##    different equations
SRAND( $psvn );

$y0 = random(2,8,1);

$a = random(2,5,1);
## the roots are -$a +/- i
##    so (r + $a)^2 = -1, or r^2 + 2 $a r + $a^2 + 1 = 0
$twoa  = 2*$a;
$asq   = $a*$a;
$asqp1 = $asq + 1;

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the solution to the initial value problem
\( y'' + $twoa y' + $asqp1 y = 0 \), \(y(0) = 0\), \(y'(0) = $y0\).

$PAR
\( y(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(Compute( "$y0*e^(-$a*t)*sin(t)" )->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The characteristic equation is \(r^2 + $twoa r + $asqp1 = 0\),
so \(r=-$a\pm i\).
$PAR
Therefore \(y(t) = A e^{-$a t}\cos t + B e^{-$a t}\sin t\).
Then
\( y'(t) = A\left(e^{-$a t}(-\sin t) + (-$a e^{-$a t})\cos t\right) +
B\left(e^{-$a t}\cos t + (-$a e^{-$a t})\sin t\right)\),
so \(y'(0) = $y0 = -$a A + B\) and
\(y(0) = 0 = A\)
$PAR
Therefore \(A = 0\), \(B = $y0\) and \(y(t) = $y0 e^{-$a t}\sin t\).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


;
ENDDOCUMENT();
